modules.description: Provides pretty-printers for error and write error types. Manages block device interactions including disconnection, information retrieval, and reading/writing data using Cstruct lists. Supports sector-based I/O operations with specific constraints on buffer alignment and size.

Provides functions to read from and write to a single file stored in a fixed-size block, using CRC32 for data integrity checks. Operates on byte sequences and block devices, ensuring consistent access to stored data. Useful for maintaining transient data like cached checksums that require frequent updates without risking data corruption.

Handles error visualization and block device communication, enabling low-level I/O operations with strict alignment and size requirements. Supports reading and writing data through Cstruct lists, along with managing device disconnections and retrieving device information. Operations include sector-based data transfers and error reporting. Examples include logging error details, reading sector data, and disconnecting from a block device.
